HEADWORD: Roselle
<hw>Ro*selle"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>a
malvaceous plant (<spn>Hibiscus Sabdariffa</spn>) cultivated in the east
and West Indies for its fleshy calyxes, which are used for making tarts
and jelly and an acid drink.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

